title: LeVitt takes third in state tennis
text:
LeVitt takes third in state tennis Jim Krajewski , jkrajewski@rgj.com 9:55 p.m. PDT October 24, 2015 Reno junior McKenna Levitt finished third in the girls Division I state tennis tournament Saturday in Las Vegas. (Photo: Andy Barron/RGJ file) CONNECT 7 TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
Reno junior McKenna LeVitt beat Palo Verde’s Kristen Newell 7-5, 6-3, in the third-place match Saturday at the Nevada state tennis tournament at the Darling Tennis Center in Las Vegas. 
In the semifinals earlier Saturday morning, Angelique Friedrich of Bishop Gorman, beat LeVitt, 6-1, 6-0. Friedrich, a freshman, went on to win the state title by beating her teammate Amber Del Rosario 6-3, 6-4. 
In Division I boys singles, Dylan Levitt from Palo Verde won the championship, beating Aaron Bailey from Bishop Gorman, 6-1, 4-6, 6-1. 
Reno’s doubles team of Ian Rinehart and Riley Boyden lost in the third-place match, 6-4, 6-4, to Mike Safbrom and Brandon Sulzberg of Palo Verde. Sam Grant and Ryland McDermott of Coronado won the title. 
Chloe Hendersona and Sophie Henderson of Palo Verde won the girls Division I doubles title. 
In the I-A boys singles, Michael Pasimio from Clark beat Zach haas from Truckee, 6-2, 6-2, to win the championship. 
In I-A boys doubles, Kevin Cross and Colin Deurlington from Truckee, won the third-place match, beating Louis Marin and Mickey Sullivan from South Tahoe, 6-5, 4-6, 6-4. 
In the I-A girls singles, Andrada Stanciu, from Sierra Vista, beat Madison Foley from Faith Lutheran 6-1, 6-1, in the final. 
In I-A girls doubles, Ava Frazier and Olivia Waysack from The Meadows won the championship. Izzy Martinez and Paige Thorne from Fallon lost in the third-place match. Read or Share this story: http://on.rgj.com/1N0iwlB TOP VIDEOS
